{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Web Agency Backend API",
    "description": "# Web Agency Backend API\n\n## Base URL\n```\nhttp://localhost:3500\n```\nChange `baseUrl` in the collection variables to match your environment.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\nThis service is an **API Gateway**. It owns a small set of routes and transparently proxies everything else to downstream microservices. All requests from your frontend go to **this single base URL**.\n\n### Routes owned by this service\n| Prefix | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `POST /api/upload/proposal` | Save a base64-encoded proposal HTML file locally |\n| `/api/newsletter/*` | Full newsletter subscription lifecycle (stored in MongoDB) |\n| `GET /api/health` | Health check |\n| `GET /api/ready` | Readiness probe (DB connected?) |\n| `GET /api/postman-collection` | Download this Postman collection |\n\n### Proxied routes (pass-through — this gateway adds no logic)\n| Prefix | Forwards to | Microservice |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/auth/*` | `AUTH_SERVICE_URL/api/auth/*` | user-auth-service (port 4002) |\n| `/api/admin/*` | `AUTH_SERVICE_URL/api/admin/*` | user-auth-service (port 4002) |\n| `/api/leads/*` | `LEAD_SERVICE_URL/api/leads/*` | lead-microservice |\n| `/api/files/*` | `FILE_UPLOAD_SERVICE_URL/api/files/*` | file-upload-service (port 4001) |\n\n---\n\n## Contact Forms & Project Inquiries\n\nBoth submit to the **same endpoint** on the lead-microservice:\n```\nPOST {{baseUrl}}/api/leads/submit\n```\nUse the `category` field to distinguish them:\n- General contact message → `\"category\": \"General Inquiry\"`\n- Project estimate request → `\"category\": \"Sales\"` + include `projectType`, `budget`, `timeline`\n\nThe lead-microservice handles storage, CRM pipeline, and all email notifications for leads.\n\n---\n\n## Authentication Flow\n1. Call `POST /api/auth/login` — the test script saves `accessToken` → `{{authToken}}`\n2. All protected requests automatically send `Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}`\n3. When the token expires, call `POST /api/auth/token/refresh` with `{{refreshToken}}`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{authToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3500",
      "description": "Base URL of the web-agency-backend-api gateway. Change for staging/production."
    },
    {
      "key": "authToken",
      "value": "",
      "description": "JWT access token — auto-set by the Login request test script."
    },
    {
      "key": "refreshToken",
      "value": "",
      "description": "JWT refresh token — auto-set by the Login request test script."
    },
    {
      "key": "leadId",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Lead ID — auto-set after submitting a lead."
    },
    {
      "key": "fileId",
      "value": "",
      "description": "File ID — auto-set after uploading a file."
    },
    {
      "key": "subscriberEmail",
      "value": "test@example.com",
      "description": "Email used for newsletter tests."
    }
  ],
